"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-09-olympic-qualifier-nigerias-dtigress-beat-senegal\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Women Basketball team, D'Tigress, on Thursday defeated Senegal 72-65 to win their first game in Group A at the FIBA Women's Olympic Qualifying event in Antwerp, Belgium.  The game saw the Afrobasket champions take the lead in the first quarter 20-18, but trailed Senegal 37-46 in the second quarter.  Senegal maintained the lead 57-49 at the end of the third quarter and trailing 57-49 heading into the last 10 minutes and looking low on energy, Nigeria dug deep.  They started the last quarter with an 11-0 run to swing the contest back firmly in their favour.  Amy Okonkwo led Nigeria with an incredible 21 points and 10 rebounds, demonstrating why she was named MVP of the FIBA Women's AfroBasket in 2023.  Nigeria endured a real roller-coaster to finish up with a win.  They will meet the United States on Friday before facing Belgium on Sunday.  Zamfara stadium renovation: Sports Council demands timely completion  AFCON: Bafana Bafana caused Super Eagles problems - Semi Ajayi  AFCON: CAF dividing Africa - Senegal's Gueye speaks on returning gold medals to Morocco  Moroccan club sack Senegal midfielder over AFCON 2025 title stripping remarks  CAF's decision to strip Senegal of AFCON title stirs controversy  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  AFCON: Very decent woman' - Gaye hails Nigerian judge after decision to strip Senegal of title  Guardiola reacts to CAF stripping Senegal of 2025 AFCON title win  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"